  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight: it analyzes discovered failures in terms of model internals and statistical patterns (layer-wise covariance/variance, density changes, out-of-range neuron outputs) and uses controlled experiments to show how different failure types (e.g., adversarial examples, adversarial perturbations) manifest in those internals. However, it does not trace discovered failures to deeper root causes such as corrupted or biased training data or specific spurious features with empirical causal evidence. While the paper notes phenomena like texture-bias and demonstrates that certain transformations (stylize/blur) reveal vulnerabilities, it does not systematically link the failures it finds to concrete underlying vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias or overfitting) beyond the internal-statistics characterization. Hence it satisfies the metric for partial diagnostic understanding but not full root-cause explanation.",
